What you need to know:

Titus Jogo, the officer in charge of the refugee desk in Obangi district, which borders Arua, said the briefing from police said the fight was triggered by quarrels over a water source.John Jal Dak, the executive director for Youth Social Advocacy Team, a civil society organisation in Rhino camp, said six refugees were confirmed dead.In July 2018, more than 40 houses of South Sudanese refugees were burned down in Ayilo Camp in Adjumani district by the host community.